tic forenames:  Spanish Carlos, Jose, Manuel, Alvaro, Diego, Edelmira, Emilio, Francisco, Gilberto, Jorge, Jose Angel.  German Gerhard, Hans, Ilse, Lutz, Manfred, Wolf.","Czech and Slovak; Sorbian (<b>Pěch</b> and <b>P'ech</b>): from a pet form of the personal name <i>Petr</i> (Czech), <i>Pětš</i> (Lower Sorbian), and   Peter   (Slovak). This is also a Germanized form of the Upper Sorbian cognate <b>Pjech</b>.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): from Middle High German <i>pech</i> (German <i>Pech</i>) ‘pitch, tar’, presumably a nickname for someone with exceptionally dark skin or hair, or a metonymic occupational name for someone who prepared, sold, or used pitch. This may in part also be the origin of a homonymic Polish, Czech, and Slovak surname (compare above and below)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Nest Fechan ferch Gwrwrad ap Gwilym was born in 1274, in Llansadwrn, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Gwrwared ap Gwilym and Gwenlian ferch Ednyfed. She married Gruffydd ap Hywel Tudor in 1300, in Carmarthenshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1274–":"1274–Surnud","1274–Female":"1274–Surnud","1255–1343":"1255–1343","1288–1356":"1288–1356","–1356":"–1356","1244–1292":"1244–1292","–Female":"Surnud","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1288":"1288","1244":"1244","1343":"1343","1255":"1255","1274":"1274","1292":"1292","Llansadwrn, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Llansadwrn, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1274–":"1274–Kuollut","1274–Female":"1274–Kuollut","1255–1343":"1255–1343","1288–1356":"1288–1356","–1356":"–1356","1244–1292":"1244–1292","–Female":"Kuollut","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1288":"1288","1244":"1244","1343":"1343","1255":"1255","1274":"1274","1292":"1292","Llansadwrn, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Llansadwrn, Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1274–":"1274–Décédée",